hm2NetConfigMib.name: hm2NetConfigMib
hm2NetConfigMib.contactinfo: Postal: Stuttgarter Str. 45-51 72654 Neckartenzlingen Germany Phone: +49 7127 140 E-mail: hac.support@belden.com
hm2NetConfigMib.description: Hirschmann Network Configuration MIB. Copyright (C) 2012. All Rights Reserved.

hm2NetConfigProtocol.name: hm2NetConfigProtocol
hm2NetConfigProtocol.description: The switch's network configuration protocol. The default value is dependent of the device type.

hm2NetLocalIPAddr.name: hm2NetLocalIPAddr
hm2NetLocalIPAddr.description: IP address of the management agent board. Changing this value will take effect after activating with hm2NetAction.

hm2NetPrefixLength.name: hm2NetPrefixLength
hm2NetPrefixLength.description: The length of the IP netmask.

hm2NetGatewayIPAddr.name: hm2NetGatewayIPAddr
hm2NetGatewayIPAddr.description: IP address of the default gateway. Changing this value will take effect after activating with hm2NetAction.

hm2NetVlanID.name: hm2NetVlanID
hm2NetVlanID.description: VLAN-ID of the IP protocol stack. The VLAN-ID value means that only traffic of the appropriate VLAN is accepted and outgoing traffic uses this VLAN-ID.

hm2NetVlanPriority.name: hm2NetVlanPriority
hm2NetVlanPriority.description: VLAN Priority which is used in management replies.

hm2NetIpDscpPriority.name: hm2NetIpDscpPriority
hm2NetIpDscpPriority.description: IP DSCP value which is used in management replies.

hm2NetMgmtPort.name: hm2NetMgmtPort
hm2NetMgmtPort.description: The port number of the Ethernet port, which gets the access to the switch management. If the value is set to 0, the access to the switch management is permitted from all ports of the switch. This object is only applicable for embedded switches which are integrated into customer devices.

hm2NetDHCPClientId.name: hm2NetDHCPClientId
hm2NetDHCPClientId.description: The identifier string that is currently used by the client in the request packets to the server for obtaining lease information.

hm2NetAction.name: hm2NetAction
hm2NetAction.description: This object, when read, always returns a value of other(1). Setting the object to activate(2) causes a reconfiguration of the IP protocol stack with the current values of hm2NetLocalIPAddr, hm2NetGatewayIPAddr and hm2NetMask.

hm2NetACDStatus.name: hm2NetACDStatus
hm2NetACDStatus.description: Sets the status of the ip address conflict detection mechanism on this device. With activating the ACD status an internal check of duplicated IP-addresses is enabled.

hm2NetACDDetectionMode.name: hm2NetACDDetectionMode
hm2NetACDDetectionMode.description: Sets the mode of the ip address conflict detection mechanism on this device. activeAndPassive (1): Both active and passive detection are active. activeDetectionOnly (2): During configuration of a local ip address the device actively probes the network for this ip address. passiveDetectionOnly (3): The device listens passively on the network if another device with an already locally configured ip address appears. In this case the own ip address is actively defended by transmitting gratituous ARP's.

hm2NetACDOngoingProbeStatus.name: hm2NetACDOngoingProbeStatus
hm2NetACDOngoingProbeStatus.description: If enabled, the device sends periodic ARP or NDP probes every 90-120 seconds.

hm2NetACDDelay.name: hm2NetACDDelay
hm2NetACDDelay.description: Time gap between ARP or NDP probes being sent.

hm2NetACDReleaseDelay.name: hm2NetACDReleaseDelay
hm2NetACDReleaseDelay.description: Delay in seconds to the next ARP or NDP probe cycle after an ip address conflict was detected.

hm2NetACDMaxProtection.name: hm2NetACDMaxProtection
hm2NetACDMaxProtection.description: The number of ARP announcement packets (gratuitous ARP packets) in passive(ongoing) mode to be received within hm2NetACDProtectInterval until the agent detects this as a conflict.

hm2NetACDProtectInterval.name: hm2NetACDProtectInterval
hm2NetACDProtectInterval.description: Delay in milliseconds between two protections. See also hm2NetACDMaxProtection.

hm2NetACDFaultState.name: hm2NetACDFaultState
hm2NetACDFaultState.description: true(1) if an active address conflict is detected. false(2) if no present address conflict.

hm2NetACDTrapEnable.name: hm2NetACDTrapEnable
hm2NetACDTrapEnable.description: If enabled this trap reports an address conflict.

hm2NetACDAddrTable.name: hm2NetACDAddrTable
hm2NetACDAddrTable.description: This table contains address conflict detection information on the local system known to this agent.

hm2NetACDAddrEntry.name: hm2NetACDAddrEntry
hm2NetACDAddrEntry.description: IP Address conflict detection information about a particular address on the local system known to this agent. There may be multiple addresses configured on the system. Entries may be created and deleted in this table by the agent.

hm2NetACDTimeMark.name: hm2NetACDTimeMark
hm2NetACDTimeMark.description: A TimeFilter for this entry. See the TimeFilter textual convention in IETF RFC 2021 and http://www.ietf.org/IESG/Implementations/RFC2021-Implementation.txt to see how TimeFilter works.

hm2NetACDIPAddr.name: hm2NetACDIPAddr
hm2NetACDIPAddr.description: IP address used to identify the management address component associated with the local system.

hm2NetACDMAC.name: hm2NetACDMAC
hm2NetACDMAC.description: The physical address of the device that was detected causing the ip address conflict.

hm2NetACDifIndex.name: hm2NetACDifIndex
hm2NetACDifIndex.description: The interface index on the local system where the ip address conflict was detected.

hm2NetLocalBurnedInMacAddr.name: hm2NetLocalBurnedInMacAddr
hm2NetLocalBurnedInMacAddr.description: Physical base address (MAC address) of the agent. This is the burned in MAC address from the production

hm2NetLocalAdminMacAddress.name: hm2NetLocalAdminMacAddress
hm2NetLocalAdminMacAddress.description: The switch's network locally administered MAC address. This is the locally MAC address from the administrator. If the hm2NetLocalAdminMacAddress is nonzero, the device starts with this MAC address at the next boot. If the variable is changed, they must be stored by the configuration manager. A MAC address with a set multicast bit will not be accepted

hm2NetMacAddressType.name: hm2NetMacAddressType
hm2NetMacAddressType.description: Shows the currently used MAC address at boot time. The device starts with the burned in MAC address when hm2NetLocalAdminMacAddress is zero, otherwise with the Local-Admin-MAC-Address.

hm2NetHiDiscoveryOperation.name: hm2NetHiDiscoveryOperation
hm2NetHiDiscoveryOperation.description: Enables/disables the HiDiscovery protocol on this device. This protocol allows a remote host to detect devices without an IP configuration. It also allows the host to set IP parameters, like the ip address, the netmask and the gateway address.

hm2NetHiDiscoveryMode.name: hm2NetHiDiscoveryMode
hm2NetHiDiscoveryMode.description: In the read only mode only detecting and reading the IP parameters is permitted. The read write mode gives full access to the device.

hm2NetHiDiscoveryBlinking.name: hm2NetHiDiscoveryBlinking
hm2NetHiDiscoveryBlinking.description: Enables/disables the HiDiscovery blinking sequence on this device. This object will not be saved.

hm2NetHiDiscoveryProtocol.name: hm2NetHiDiscoveryProtocol
hm2NetHiDiscoveryProtocol.description: Shows the HiDiscovery protocols supported by the device.

hm2NetMacACDStatus.name: hm2NetMacACDStatus
hm2NetMacACDStatus.description: Sets the status of the MAC address conflict detection mechanism on this device.

hm2NetMacACDConflictAddress.name: hm2NetMacACDConflictAddress
hm2NetMacACDConflictAddress.description: MAC address in case of a conflict.

hm2NetACDNotification.name: hm2NetACDNotification
hm2NetACDNotification.description: This trap reports an address conflict.

hm2NetMacACDNotification.name: hm2NetMacACDNotification
hm2NetMacACDNotification.description: This trap reports a MAC address conflict with it's own MAC address.

hm2NetOobMgmtAdminState.name: hm2NetOobMgmtAdminState
hm2NetOobMgmtAdminState.description: The status of the Out-of-band management on this device.

hm2NetOobMgmtProtocol.name: hm2NetOobMgmtProtocol
hm2NetOobMgmtProtocol.description: The switch's out-of-band network configuration protocol. The default value is dependent of the device type.

hm2NetOobMgmtIPAddr.name: hm2NetOobMgmtIPAddr
hm2NetOobMgmtIPAddr.description: Out-of-band IP address of the management agent board. Changing this value will take effect after activating with hm2NetOobMgmtAction.

hm2NetOobMgmtPrefixLength.name: hm2NetOobMgmtPrefixLength
hm2NetOobMgmtPrefixLength.description: The length of the IP netmask.

hm2NetOobMgmtGatewayIPAddrType.name: hm2NetOobMgmtGatewayIPAddrType
hm2NetOobMgmtGatewayIPAddrType.description: Out-of-band default gateway IP address type.

hm2NetOobMgmtGatewayIPAddr.name: hm2NetOobMgmtGatewayIPAddr
hm2NetOobMgmtGatewayIPAddr.description: Out-of-band IP address of the default gateway. Changing this value will take effect after activating with hm2NetOobMgmtAction.

hm2NetOobMgmtMacAddress.name: hm2NetOobMgmtMacAddress
hm2NetOobMgmtMacAddress.description: Out-of-band MAC address of the interface.

hm2NetOobMgmtAction.name: hm2NetOobMgmtAction
hm2NetOobMgmtAction.description: This object, when read, always returns a value of other(1). Setting the object to activate(2) causes a reconfiguration of the out-of-band IP protocol stack with the current values of hm2NetOobMgmtLocalIPAddr, hm2NetOobMgmtPrefixLength and hm2NetOobMgmtGatewayIPAddr.
